HEADWORD: Doornail
<hw>Door"nail`</hw> <pr>(d⟦omac⟧r"n⟦amac⟧l`)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<def>The nail or knob on which in ancient doors the knocker struck; --
hence the old saying, ⟦ldquo⟧As dead as a
<xex>doornail</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Doorplane</ent>⟦br⟧
